HTTP client inspired by curlie/httpie.

Supports httpie-like syntax for headers and data:
  key:value     HTTP header
  key=value     JSON data field
  key==value    URL query parameter
  @file         Request body from file

Methods: GET, POST, PUT, DELETE, PATCH, HEAD, OPTIONS

Examples:
  omni curl https:<PATH>
  omni curl POST https:<PATH> name=John email=john@example.com
  omni curl https:<PATH> Authorization:"Bearer token"
  omni curl https:<PATH> q==hello
  omni curl POST https:<PATH> @data.json
  omni curl -v https:<PATH>
  omni curl --json https:<PATH>

Usage:
  omni curl [METHOD] URL [ITEM...] [flags]

Flags:
  -d, --data string          request body data
  -f, --form                 send as form data instead of JSON
  -H, --header stringArray   custom header (can be used multiple times)
  -h, --help                 help for curl
  -k, --insecure             skip TLS verification
      --json                 output response as structured JSON
  -L, --location             follow redirects (default true)
  -t, --timeout int          request timeout in seconds (default 30)
  -v, --verbose              show request/response details

Global Flags:
      --table   output as aligned table
